BERLIN (AP) — Berlin Airport canceled all its flights Wednesday after ground staff went on strike to press their demands for higher pay.The walk-out affected about 300 flights to and from Germany’s capital.Labor union Verdi said its members were seeking a raise of 500 euros ($544) per month. German news agency dpa reported that employers have offered staff a one-off payment of 2,000 euros.Germany experienced its highest annual inflation in more than 70 years last year.Sharp increases in the cost of food and energy saw full-year inflation reach 7.9% in 2022.